&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="v-show-vs-v-if">v-show vs. v-if
&lt;/h2>&lt;table>
&lt;thead>
&lt;tr>
&lt;th>Feature&lt;/th>
&lt;th>v-show&lt;/th>
&lt;th>v-if&lt;/th>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;/thead>
&lt;tbody>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Purpose&lt;/td>
&lt;td>Toggles visibility&lt;/td>
&lt;td>Toggles visibility (conditional rendering)&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Syntax&lt;/td>
&lt;td>v-show=&amp;ldquo;expression&amp;rdquo;&lt;/td>
&lt;td>v-if=&amp;ldquo;expression&amp;rdquo;&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Value&lt;/td>
&lt;td>true shows, false hides&lt;/td>
&lt;td>true shows, false hides&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Mechanism&lt;/td>
&lt;td>Toggles &lt;code>style=&amp;quot;display:none;&amp;quot;&lt;/code>&lt;/td>
&lt;td>Directly adds or removes elements from DOM&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;tr>
&lt;td>Scenario&lt;/td>
&lt;td>Frequent toggling&lt;/td>
&lt;td>Infrequent toggling&lt;/td>
&lt;/tr>
&lt;/tbody>
&lt;/table>
&lt;h2 id="v-else-and-v-else-if">v-else and v-else-if
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Used to assist &lt;code>v-if&lt;/code> for conditional rendering. Must be placed immediately after a &lt;code>v-if&lt;/code> or &lt;code>v-else-if&lt;/code> element.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Simple Vue Project</title><link>https://blog.yexca.net/en/archives/173/</link><pubDate>Tue, 28 May 2024 16:22:15 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://blog.yexca.net/en/archives/173/</guid><description>&lt;div class="notice ">&lt;strong>📢&lt;/strong> This article was translated by gemini-2.5-flash
&lt;/div>
&lt;p>In early full-stack development, communication overhead was high, roles were fuzzy, and it was tough to manage or extend projects.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Today&amp;rsquo;s standard is frontend-backend separation, driven by API documentation.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="frontend-backend-separation">Frontend-Backend Separation
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Frontend sends parameters and parses response data based on API docs. Backend receives parameters and responds as per API docs.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Dev Workflow: Requirements Analysis -&amp;gt; API Definition (API Docs) -&amp;gt; Parallel Frontend/Backend Dev (following specs) -&amp;gt; Testing -&amp;gt; Frontend/Backend Integration Testing.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>